美股度过金融危机以来最黑暗一周，美联储表态。
U. S. stocks weathered the worst week of the financial crisis, the Fed said.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
澎湃新闻记者 孙铭蔚 综合报道当地时间2月28日，因担忧新冠肺炎疫情持续扩散，美股三大股指大幅低开，道琼斯工业指数一度再次跌掉超过1000点，但盘中美联储表态采取适当措施提振经济，以及微软引领大型科技股反弹，美股收复了部分失地。
BEIJING, Feb. 28 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell more than 1,000 points in the wake of concerns about the continued spread of the outbreak, but U.S. stocks regained some of their ground after the Fed said it would take appropriate measures to boost the economy and Microsoft led a rebound in big technology stocks.
截至收盘，标普500下跌24.60点，跌幅0.83%，报2954.14点；纳斯达克指数上涨0.90点，涨幅0.01%，报8567.37点；道琼斯指数下跌357.50点，跌幅1.39%，报25409.15点。
By the end of trading, the S & P 500 was down 24.60 points, or 0.83%, at 2954.14; the Nasdaq was up 0.90 points, or 0.01%, at 8567.37; and the Dow Jones Industrial Average was down 357.50 points, or 1.39%, at 25409.15.
标普500指数的11个板块中有8个板块下跌，3个板块上涨。
Eight of the 11 S & P 500 sectors fell and three rose.
其中，公用事业板块领跌，能源板块领涨。
Among them, utilities led the decline, energy plate led the rise.
本周（2月24日至2月28日）美股创下2008年金融危机以来的最差一周表现。
US stocks this week (Feb. 24 to Feb. 28) had their worst week since the 2008 financial crisis.
道指本周累跌逾12%，创2008年以来最大单周百分比跌幅，与2月12日创下的纪录高点相比累跌14.1%；按点数来看，累计跌幅超过3500点。
The Dow is down more than 12 per cent this week, its biggest weekly percentage loss since 2008, down 14.1 per cent from a record high set on February 12 and more than 3,500 points in points.
标普500指数本周累跌11.5%，创金融危机以来最大单周跌幅。
The S & P 500 fell 11.5% this week, its biggest weekly decline since the financial crisis.
美国大型科技股涨跌不一，苹果跌0.06%，亚马逊跌0.03%，奈飞跌0.72%，谷歌涨1.85%，Facebook涨1.43%，微软涨2.42%，特斯拉跌1.62%。
Major U.S. technology stocks were mixed, with Apple down 0.06%, Amazon down 0.03%, Naifei down 0.72%, Google up 1.85%, Facebook up 1.43%, Microsoft up 2.42%, Tesla down 1.62%.
热门中概股多数上涨，阿里巴巴涨1.49%，京东涨0.29%，百度涨0.06%；虎牙直播涨7%，搜狗涨6.8%，360金融涨6.09%，拼多多涨1.71%；达内科技跌31.87%，第九城市跌20%，无忧英语跌14.73%，蔚来汽车跌0.36%。
Most popular stocks rose 1.49 per cent in Alibaba, 0.29 per cent in Beijing and 0.06 per cent in Baidu, 7 per cent in Tiger Tooth, 6.8 per cent in search of dogs and 6.09 per cent in financial terms, up 1.71 per cent. Daney technology fell 31.87 per cent, ninth city 20 per cent, (www.51education.net)
欧洲股市在周五的交易中延续本周以来历史性的大跌走势。
European stocks continued their historic slide this week in trading on Friday.
欧洲斯托克600指数下跌13.80点，报收于375.65点，跌幅为3.54%，本周累跌12.7%，创下了自2008年10月份全球金融危机高峰时期以来的最大单周跌幅。
The European stock market index fell 13.80 points, or 3.54 per cent, to 375.65, dropping 12.7 per cent this week, its biggest weekly decline since the peak of the global financial crisis in October 2008.
德国DAX 30指数下跌3.86%，报收于11890.35点；英国富时100指数下跌3.18%，报收于6580.61点；法国CAC 40指数下跌3.38%，报收于5309.90点；意大利富时MIB指数下跌3.58%，报收于21984.21点。
The German DAX 30 index fell 3.86 per cent to 11890.35, the FTSE 100 fell 3.18 per cent to 6580.61, the CAC 40 index fell 3.38 per cent to 5309.90 and the FTSE MIB index fell 3.58 per cent to 21,984.21.
新冠病毒继续在全球传播，目前已有82000多例确诊病例，造成2800多例死亡。
The new crown virus continues to spread around the world, with more than 82,000 confirmed cases and more than 2,800 deaths.
世界卫生组织总干事谭德塞2月28日宣布，将新冠肺炎疫情全球风险级别由此前的“高”上调为“非常高”。
The World Health Organization (WHO) Director-General Theresa Tupper announced February 28, the new crown pneumonia global risk level from the previous "high" to "very high.
新冠肺炎疫情在全球蔓延加剧了市场的恐慌情绪，但美联储没什么新意的表态还是给市场注入了一针强心剂。
The global spread of the New Crown Pneumonia has added to market fears, but the Fed's lack of innovation has given the market a shot in the arm.
美联储主席鲍威尔（Jerome Powell）2月28日表示，美联储正在监测新型冠状病毒对美国经济构成的风险，并承诺在必要时采取行动。
US Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell said Feb. 28 that the Federal Reserve was monitoring the risks posed to the US economy by the new coronavirus and promised to take action if necessary.
鲍威尔说：“美国经济的基本面仍然强劲。
"The fundamentals of the US economy remain strong," Powell said.
然而，新型冠状病毒对经济活动构成了不断演变的风险。
However, the new coronavirus poses an evolving risk to economic activity.
美联储正在密切关注事态发展及其对经济前景的影响。
The Fed is closely watching developments and their implications for the economic outlook.
我们将使用我们的工具，采取适当的行动来支持经济。
We will use our tools to take appropriate action to support the economy.
”声明中的实际语言与鲍威尔和其他美联储官员先前的声明几乎没有什么不同。
The actual language in the statement is little different from previous statements by Powell and other Fed officials.
然而，在此股市出现了恶性下跌，人们担心新冠病毒的蔓延可能危及全球经济增长之际，鲍威尔的言论令市场颇感欣慰，随后美国股市和现货金银纷纷缩减跌幅，美元指数则承压下跌。
However, Mr. Powell's comments came as markets were cheered by a vicious decline in the stock market and fears that the spread of the new cap virus could threaten global economic growth, followed by a decline in US stocks and cash gold and silver, and a fall in the dollar index.
“我希望美联储能够参与进来，我希望他们能尽快参与进来，”特朗普在周五下午晚些时候表示。
"I wanted the Fed to be involved, and I wanted them to get involved as soon as possible," Trump said late Friday afternoon.
特朗普没有特别提出降息要求，但他表示，随着人们越来越担心疫情会导致经济急剧放缓，美联储应该跟随其“投入大量资金”的全球同行。
Trump did not specifically ask for a rate cut, but he said the Fed should follow his global peers "who have invested a lot of money" as fears mount that the outbreak could lead to a sharp economic slowdown.
“他们全都投入了很多钱。
"They put a lot of money into it all.
我们的美联储坐在那儿，没有做他们应该做的事，”特朗普说， “他们（指美联储）给我们国家带来了极大的伤害。
Our Federal Reserve sits there, not doing what it should, "Trump said." They are doing our country a great disservice. "
”高盛周五表示，疫情可能使全球GDP在第一季度下降0.5个百分点、二季度下降0.2%，并刺激美联储和全球其他央行降低利率。
Goldman Sachs said Friday the outbreak could cut global GDP by 0.5 percentage points in the first quarter, 0.2 per cent in the second quarter and spur the Federal Reserve and other central banks around the world to cut interest rates.
高盛预计，美联储今年首次降息可能发生在3月份，上半年则将总共降息75个基点。
Goldman Sachs expects the Fed to cut interest rates for the first time this year, possibly in March, for a total of 75 basis points in the first half.
美国银行经济学家目前预计，美联储将于3月的会议上降息50个基点，以遏制市场的恐慌情绪，同时为经济增长提供支撑。
Bank of America economists now expect the Fed to cut interest rates by 50 basis points at its March meeting to stem market panic and support economic growth.
是否在会议前进行紧急降息将取决于市场失灵的程度。
Whether an emergency rate cut takes place before the meeting will depend on the extent of market failure.
“股市这次遭遇抛售最大的问题之一可能是，抛售是在月底到来的。
"One of the biggest problems with the sell-off may be that it came at the end of the month."
”资产管理公司Capitol Securities Management的首席经济策略师肯特·恩格尔克(Kent Engelke)在周五接受采访时表示，“我真的认为，很多人都没有意识到正在发生的‘大屠杀’。
"I really don't think a lot of people are aware of the carnage taking place," Kent Engelke, chief economic strategist at Capitol Securities Management, said in an interview on Friday.
问题在于，当人们在3月1日看到自己的月度账单时，他们会作何反应？““就被拉高了的投资者情绪而言，（此次病毒爆发）是在最糟糕的时机到来的。
The problem is, how do people react when they see their monthly statements on March 1st? In terms of increased investor sentiment, [the outbreak] comes at the worst possible moment.
”总部设在明尼阿波利斯的美国投资研究公司路佛集团（The Leuthold Group）的首席投资官道格-拉姆齐（Doug Ramsey）在谈到新冠病毒爆发时表示，“我不确定市场是否真的消化了这件事的潜在经济影响。
Doug Ramsey, chief investment officer at The Leuthold Group, a Minneapolis-based investment-research firm, said of the outbreak of the new cap virus: "I'm not sure the market has really digested the potential economic impact of this.
”意大利裕信银行(UniCredit Bank)的分析师表示，可能需要有明确的迹象表明新冠病毒确诊病例数量趋于平稳，才能让股市见底。
Analysts at UniCredit Bank said there might be a need for clear signs that the number of confirmed cases of the new crown virus would stabilise before the stock market could bottom out.
但根据最新的统计数据，这看起来不太可能在未来几天内实现。
But according to the latest statistics, this looks unlikely to happen in the next few days.
随着股市暴跌势头的加剧，美国国债和其他核心政府债券上涨，压低了与债券价格走势相反的收益率。
As the stock market plummeted, Treasurys and other core government bonds rose, driving down yields in contrast to bond prices.
裕信银行分析师在一份研究报告中写道：“因此，股市的暴跌、以及随之而来的美国国债和德国国债收益率的持续下降势头，很可能还没有结束。
"As a result, the plunge in the stock market and the subsequent steady decline in yields on US Treasury and German bonds are probably not over yet," Hiroshi bank analysts wrote in a research note
”本期编辑 常琛推荐阅读。
